I bought this and i was worried that it might not fit me. But it fits me even better than it fits her. And I'm totally in love with it. This girl (miscusi.etsy.com) uses all recycled items. Like she'll go to a thrift store and find a bulky gross christmas sweater that your mom probably gave you, and she'll unravel it, clean, steam the kinks of the yarn, and knit it into a scarf or a hat. In this case with the vintage slipdress she died and screenprinted. I think she's wicked. :)

Ingredients

 

2 tbsp.              Raisins

2 tbsp.              Onion (finely chopped)

2 tbsp.              Balsamic Vinegar

2 tbsp.              Water

2 tbsp.              Italian Salad Dressing

9                      Jumbo White Mushrooms

1/3 cups           Walnut Pieces

                        Salt & Pepper)

 

Directions

 

1)      In a small saucepan over medium-high heat, combine raisins, onion, balsamic vinegar, and water for about 5 minutes.

 

2)      Take out stems of mushrooms and brush Italian salad dressing on mushrooms, so that all surfaces are evenly coated.

 

3)      Set on a greased baking sheet.

 

4)      Put chopped mushroom stems in caps, along with walnut pieces, and raisin-onion-vinegar mix. Put salt and pepper.

 

5)      Preheat over to 375 F (190 C), and bake for 20 minutes.

 

6)      Enjoy J
